narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: More Spanish? Just kidding. I got to practice speaking more and review grammar.
I gained a better understanding of the subjunctive form and certain vocabulary words.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Weird exam structure, filling in the blank is not an effective way to test production of grammar?  Otherwise, Professor was great and the pace is decent.
I thought there should be more ways of engaging with the material.

great consistency and effective homework assignments
struggled to improve my speaking/listening skills
Weakness is that many students in L3 should have been placed lower; difficult to practice speaking when people dont have the skills.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I mean if you want to or have to learn Spanish what choice do you have?
Yesyou can learn a lot, but it comes with its downsides. Its a lot of work and it may be taught on the quicker side.
